@arkash, can you please change the title to: `[BEAM-3246] Bigtable: Merge splits if they exceed 15K`

Other than that, this looks like a copy of [existing code in CloudBigtableIO](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/cloud-bigtable-client/blob/bigtable-client-1.1.0/bigtable-dataflow-parent/bigtable-hbase-beam/src/main/java/com/google/cloud/bigtable/beam/CloudBigtableIO.java#L233).

I have one minor request.  It turns out that 15,360 works in most cases, but not always; making it configurable would be a nice to have.

Other than that, LGTM.

@chamikaramj, how can I get a Beam reviewer for this PR?

@kennknowles I am not sure if there's a better workaround for this.

Current developments from Jira:

@dkulp found that simply referencing `SqlTypeName.VARCHAR` in the test reproduces the issue. 
This seems to be because `SqlTypeName` has a static field that is [initialized with help of `Util` class](https://github.com/apache/calcite/blob/cb8376b13ad50003134e398a87161bec68908606/core/src/main/java/org/apache/calcite/sql/type/SqlTypeName.java#L138), which in turn has a static member that [will initialize SaffronProperties](https://github.com/apache/calcite/blob/cb8376b13ad50003134e398a87161bec68908606/core/src/main/java/org/apache/calcite/util/Util.java#L142) if it wasn't initialized before. 

So it looks like we need to override the saffron properties before we use even the `SqlTypeName` anywhere. We can do it either by providing a `saffron.properties` file in the working dir, or overriding the system properties.
